Here are all the findings, organized by question:

---

## 1. How Text IDs Are Generated for Existing Entities

There are **two distinct ID strategies** in this codebase:

### A. Auto-incrementing `serial()` integers (most application tables)

These tables use `serial().primaryKey()` — PostgreSQL auto-generates the ID, no application-side ID generation needed:

| Table | File | ID Column |
|-------|------|-----------|
| `tasks` | `/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/db-schemas/task.ts:34` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `taskLinks` | `...task.ts:52` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `taskEvents` | `...task.ts:74` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `clients` | `/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/db-schemas/client.ts:28` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `clientEvents` | `...client.ts:55` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `clientContracts` | `/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/db-schemas/client-contract.ts:33` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `contractEvents` | `...client-contract.ts:63` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `reminders` | `/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/db-schemas/reminder.ts:19` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `notifications` | `/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/db-schemas/notification.ts:37` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `prospects` | `/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/db-schemas/prospect.ts:20` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `prospectEvents` | `...prospect.ts:39` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `jobMandates` | `/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/db-schemas/job-mandate.ts:41` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `mandateEvents` | `...job-mandate.ts:63` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `prospectMandates` | `/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/db-schemas/prospect-mandate.ts:28` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |
| `prospectMandateEvents` | `...prospect-mandate.ts:55` | `id: serial().primaryKey()` |

### B. Text IDs via `crypto.randomUUID()` (auth tables + filter views)

These tables use `text("id").primaryKey()` — the ID must be supplied at insert time. The application uses `crypto.randomUUID()`:

**`user`, `session`, `account`, `verification`** — defined in `/home/aditya/projects/alpauls-ats/src/db-schemas/auth.ts`:
```ts
